      "citation_count": 3,
      "latency_seconds": 5.899,
      "answer": "The decision on whether packaging data should become separate article records is made by the business owner, who clarifies whether the packaging need is operational, descriptive, or regulatory [3][5]. Additionally, the logistics owner owns packaging concepts that affect receiving, return, stock-like handling, or supply-chain movement, which could influence this decision [4]. However, the specific role responsible for deciding on separate article records is the business owner based on their clarification of the packaging need [3]."
