      "answer": "Based on the evidence provided [1], [4] and [5], the following elements should be complete before a supplier can be used in downstream processes:\n\n- A formal request from a business team for supplier setup.\n- Completion of due diligence and credit checks.\n- Linking the supplier to required commercial contracts, service contracts, and payment contracts.\n- Mandatory fields on the supplier record must be completed meaningfully.\n- Supplier identifiers must be mapped between the procurement-side master data environment and the finance-side master data environment.\n\nThese elements ensure that the supplier is ready for operational use and prevent incomplete setup from causing downstream processes to fail."
